The paper discusses the challenges of engineering wireless sensing systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on improving the reliability and efficiency of wireless sensor systems, which is a key concern in the field of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper introduces a new protocol framework for atomic commit, which is a topic in the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also addresses the issue of radio interference, which is a concern in the field of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Dependable and Secure Computing (cs.DSN).
